The paper deals with security issues in the in-vehicle CAN network, proposing a novel identification method to detect compromised or alien ECUs being used in a replay attack. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and network security (cs.NI). The paper also mentions the use of Information and Communications (ICT) technology and electronic control units (ECUs), which are related to software engineering (cs.SE) and systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper utilizes a classification algorithm, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
